</ul>
<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Pythia&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.isidore-of-seville.com/oracles/" class="external text" title="http://www.isidore-of-seville.com/oracles/" rel="nofollow">The Oracle of Delphi and Ancient Oracles</a> edited by Tim Spalding (also <a href="http://www.isidore-of-seville.com/oracles/12.html" class="external text" title="http://www.isidore-of-seville.com/oracles/12.html" rel="nofollow">44 pictures of Delphi</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.delphicoracle.net" class="external text" title="http://www.delphicoracle.net" rel="nofollow">The Oracle of Apollo</a> is an online tribute to the magic and mystery of the Delphic Oracle.</li>
<li><a href="http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/08/0814_delphioracle.html" class="external text" title="http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/08/0814_delphioracle.html" rel="nofollow">National Geographic article</a> describes how ethylene might have been released into the environment and provoked "oracular" activity.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.greecetaxi.gr/index/delphi%20oracle.html" class="external text" title="http://www.greecetaxi.gr/index/delphi%20oracle.html" rel="nofollow">Greece Taxi: The Oracle of Delphi</a> good summary of the site</li>
<li><a href="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=0009BD34-398C-1F0A-97AE80A84189EEDF" class="external text" title="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=0009BD34-398C-1F0A-97AE80A84189EEDF" rel="nofollow">Scientific American: The Delphic Oracle</a> article which most media articles are derived.</li>
</ul>


